<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-471-401  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 471 401.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Design  Sept 10 1990 v29 n18 p14(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Don't link - integrate. (concurrent engineering)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Turino, Jon.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Concurrent engineering within a computer-aided engineering (CAE)framework is a better approach than the concept of serialengineering.andP;  The systematic approach to the integrated,simultaneous design of products and their related processes,including manufacturing, test and support, shortens the time froma design's conception to delivery.andP;  Testability, producibility,and reliability all have to be tested by team managers during thedesign phase.andP;  Management commitment and support are necessary forcreating a concurrent engineering environment within a company.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Concurrent ProgrammingComputer-Aided EngineeringManufacturingIntegrated SystemsAutomation.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>